<title type="html"><![CDATA[How do i reorder nsf tracks?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1700&amp;p=14593#p14593"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br /><em>Example for DW3: AA BD <strong>68 BB</strong> 4C <strong>04 B9</strong> </em><br /></div><br /><br />Just to make things seem a little less cryptic, that is machine code for this:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent"> TAX<br /> LDA $BB68,X<br /> JMP $B904<br /></div><br /><br />It's starting with the song # in A, moving it to X, then using X as an index into your new song order table.  Then jumping off to the init address, with a new song # in A.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Mon Jun 26, 2006 8:54 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
